		<h2 class="why_title">Why DNSSocial?</h2>

		<div class="home_features" id="tab1">
			<ul class="">
				<li>
					<div class="feature_img fleft">
						<%= image_tag 'static/why/DNS Record.png' %>
					</div><!-- feature_img close -->
					<div class="feature_desc fright">
						<h2>Record Supported</h2>
						<p>DNSSocial supports all DNS record types including A, CNAME, MX, NS, TXT, AAAA, SRV, etc.</p>
					</div><!-- feature_desc close -->
				</li>
				<li>
					<div class="feature_desc fleft">
						<h2>Vanity nameservers module</h2>
						<p>We are giving you freedom to change your name server to your liking. By using vanity nameserver, you can hide DNSSocial name server and use your own domain as your name server. Now that is a convenient feature when you want a consistent info when people WHOIS your domain.</p>
					</div><!-- feature_desc close -->
					<div class="feature_img fright">
						<%= image_tag 'static/why/Vanity NS.png' %>
					</div><!-- feature_img close -->
				</li>
				<li>
					<div class="feature_img fleft">
						<%= image_tag 'static/why/Short URL.png' %>
					</div><!-- feature_img close -->
					<div class="feature_desc fright">
						<h2>Short URL and URL Forwarding</h2>
						<p>Setting DNS Forwarding and Short URL has never been easier using DNSSocial. You can add wildcard to your DNS Forwarding and also setup Short URL for a ling URL.</p>
					</div><!-- feature_desc close -->
				</li>
				<li>
					<div class="feature_desc fleft">
						<h2>Dynamic DNS</h2>
						<p>Your server does not have Static IP? DDNS is available for you to use. So you can host your website using your dynamic ip and we take care the DNS resolving for you. </p>
					</div><!-- feature_desc close -->
					<div class="feature_img fright">
						<%= image_tag 'static/why/Dynamic DNS.png' %>
					</div><!-- feature_img close -->
				</li>
				<li>
					<div class="feature_img fleft">
						<%= image_tag 'static/why/International Domain Names.png' %>
					</div><!-- feature_img close -->
					<div class="feature_desc fright">
						<h2>IDN supported</h2>
						<p>You use non-ASCII in your domain? No problem, DNSSocial support International Domain Names (IDN), so your non-english visitor can surf to your website with their own language and characters.</p>
					</div><!-- feature_desc close -->
				</li>
			</ul>	
		</div><!-- home_desc close -->

		<div class="home_features" id="tab2">
			<ul class="">
				<li>
					<div class="feature_img fleft">
						<%= image_tag 'static/why/Global NS.png' %>
					</div><!-- feature_img close -->
					<div class="feature_desc fright">
						<h2>Globally located NS</h2>
						<p>Our NS server are located at strategic place globally. All DNS resolutions are routed to the nearest server to reduce latency and provide redundancy.</p>
					</div><!-- feature_desc close -->
				</li>
				<li>
					<div class="feature_desc fleft">
						<h2>Update in Realtime</h2>
						<p>All change made at DNSSocial are updated and propagated to other server in realtime. You won't lose a second in your life time again.</p>
					</div><!-- feature_desc close -->
					<div class="feature_img fright">
						<%= image_tag 'static/why/Update Realtime.png' %>
					</div><!-- feature_img close -->
				</li>
				<li>
					<div class="feature_img fleft">
						<%= image_tag 'static/why/Minimum TTL.png' %>
					</div><!-- feature_img close -->
					<div class="feature_desc fright">
						<h2>Minimum TTL 5 Min</h2>
						<p>3600 TTL is too long for your DDNS? We provide you with only 5 minutes TTL, so you can update faster and work efficiently faster.</p>
					</div><!-- feature_desc close -->
				</li>
				<li class="hide">
					<div class="feature_desc fleft">
						<h2>DNS view</h2>
						<p>Coming Soon.</p>
